<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="KR5c0124" type="notes"><teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>Research Notes for 列子</title><editor role="creator">TLS Project</editor></titleStmt><publicationStmt><p>published electronically as part of the TLS project at https://hxwd.org</p><availability status="2">This work has been licensed for use in the TLS</availability></publicationStmt><sourceDesc><bibl><title>Research Notes</title></bibl><p>Comments and notes to <bibl corresp="#KR5c0124"><title xml:lang="och">列子</title></bibl>.</p></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><creation resp="#CH">Initially created: <date>2022-04-23T00:28:18.753+09:00</date> by CH</creation></profileDesc></teiHeader><text><body><div><head>Comments</head><p xml:id="KR5c0124-start"><seg corresp="#KR5c0124_tls_005-6a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-09T16:05:02.421+09:00"/><seg corresp="#KR5c0124_tls_005-6a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-09T16:04:53.676+09:00">These two lines invite "or" in English, but they remain quantifiers.</seg><seg corresp="#KR5c0124_tls_003-6a.53" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-10T13:47:37.94+09:00">whether I am dreaming or not dreaming</seg><seg corresp="#KR5c0124_tls_003-6a.54" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-10T13:48:10.095+09:00">is what I am incapable of deciding.</seg><seg corresp="#KR5c0124_tls_008-6a.52" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-10T13:52:14.701+09:00">In undertakings there never is a permanent</seg><seg corresp="#KR5c0124_tls_008-6a.51" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-10T13:58:49.482+09:00">Moreover, in principles there is never an unchanging rightness;</seg><seg corresp="#KR5c0124_tls_008-6a.53" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-10T13:54:22.833+09:00">What on an earlier day one applied</seg><seg corresp="#KR5c0124_tls_008-6a.54" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-10T13:54:32.231+09:00">today one may reject;</seg><seg corresp="#KR5c0124_tls_008-6a.55" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-10T13:54:45.395+09:00">and what today one is rejecting</seg><seg corresp="#KR5c0124_tls_008-6a.56" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-10T13:55:00.512+09:00">one might later on apply.</seg><seg corresp="#KR5c0124_tls_008-6a.57" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-10T14:15:56.455+09:00">Regarding (the rules of) this matter of either using or rejecting</seg><seg corresp="#KR5c0124_tls_008-6a.58" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-10T13:57:08.922+09:00">there is no fixed right or wrong.</seg><seg corresp="#KR5c0124_tls_008-6a.45" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-10T14:11:12.211+09:00">As a matter of general principle he who hits the right moment will thrive</seg><seg corresp="#KR5c0124_tls_008-6a.46" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-10T14:11:25.913+09:00">and he who misses the right moment will be ruined.</seg><seg corresp="#KR5c0124_tls_008-6a.47" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-10T14:12:24.691+09:00">Your Way is similar to ours,</seg><seg corresp="#KR5c0124_tls_008-6a.48" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-10T14:13:12.008+09:00">but (your) achievements are different from mine.</seg><seg corresp="#KR5c0124_tls_008-6a.49" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-10T14:13:29.104+09:00">But that is a matter of missing the right moment,</seg><seg corresp="#KR5c0124_tls_008-6a.50" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-10T14:14:20.093+09:00">and it is not a matter of faultiness of the act itself.</seg><seg corresp="#KR5c0124_tls_004-5a.41" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-15T17:00:27.488+09:00">The locus classicus for the idea is Zhuangzi: 得意而不言 "He who has got hold of the idea disregards words"            列子冲虚真经评点八卷 p. 188: 無言：忘言也。</seg><seg corresp="#KR5c0124_tls_004-5a.44" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-12T10:35:06.206+09:00">謂其雖忘言而無字</seg></p></div></body></text></TEI>